data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType` to combine the cast and null check, making the test clearer and producing a better failure message:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

The generic `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>` (MSTest 3.x+) asserts the type **and** returns the typed instance, so you can keep using `handler` without a manual cast. It also gives a descriptive failure message instead of an `InvalidCastException`.
